Turkish soldier killed in clash with group at Syrian border - army
ISTANBUL (Reuters) - A Turkish soldier was killed on Sunday evening after Turkeyâ€™s security forces clashed with a group at the Syrian border seeking to enter Turkey illegally, the armed forces said in a statement.
The Turkish military, which regularly detains people seeking to cross illegally back and forth across the Syrian border, said in its statement on Monday the clash occurred in the Yayladagi area of Hatay province at 7:15 p.m. (1715 GMT).